   By Dylan Baddour November 6, 2014

Delia Garza says Austin residents of Del Valle must drive to Bastrop for closest
grocery

   Delia Garza, newly elected to the Austin City Council, said during her
   campaign that Austinites on the city’s southeastern fringe have to leave
   town and drive to the next county to find the closest grocery store.

"Families in Del Valle, who are city of Austin residents, have to drive to
   Bastrop to go to the closest grocery store," Garza said.

By phone, Gomez told us Del Valle residents have to drive 20 miles to the
